abstract: >-
  ATLAS (Active-inference Training with Learned Adaptive Stigmergy) is a
  pure Rust AGI training framework with zero external crate dependencies —
  the SQLite principle applied to AI infrastructure. It fuses five
  architectural innovations across 21 crates and 426 tests: (1) ASTRA-dev,
  an autonomous discovery engine generating live causal training data from
  NASA/WHO/World Bank/ArXiv APIs in ~10s cycles; (2) GraphPalace, a
  stigmergic memory palace where 5-type pheromone trails guide the training
  curriculum across runs, achieving O(1/√T) convergence (R²=0.982, BUTTERS);
  (3) DeepSupervisionTrainer with N_sup=4..16 forward passes per batch and
  latent carry, validated by TRM (>75% gain from N_sup, arXiv:2510.04871);
  (4) GPU-accelerated inference on Tesla T4 — 29 tok/s vs 5 tok/s CPU
  (5.8× speedup), with GPU-resident hidden state and custom CUDA kernels for
  rmsnorm/rope/silu_mul/AdamW; and (5) an OpenAI-compatible HTTP inference
  API (atlas-api) with SSE streaming and CORS support. Safety is enforced by
  a Horn-clause tractable constitution of 8 principles across 4 domains
  (Young 2026). Storage is abstracted behind the PalaceBackend trait for
  pluggable backends. ZK Schnorr proof chains link every LLM output to live
  API provenance. ATLAS is an open source contribution from OpenHub Research
  (Thailand).
